headline: Lockheed Martin Announces Fourth-Quarter and Full-Year 2025 Earnings Results Webcast
summary: Lockheed Martin (NYSE: LMT) will webcast live its fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 earnings results conference call (listen-only mode) on Thursday, Jan. 29, 2026, at 8:30 a.m. ET. Jim Taiclet, chairman, president and CEO; Evan Scott, chief financial officer; and Maria Ricciardone, vice president, Treasurer and Investor Relations, will discuss fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 results, provide updates on key topics and answer questions. Fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 results will be published

headline: L3Harris to Sell Rocket-Engine Business to Buyout Firm
summary: Defense contractor L3Harris Technologies struck a deal to sell a controlling interest in a business that makes engines that power spacecraft. Private equity firm AE Industrial Partners will acquire a roughly 60% stake in the Aerojet Rocketdyne product lines, including the RL-10 engines used on part of United Launch Alliance’s Vulcan Centaur rocket.
